Two issues in the Day 7 materials: a CSS selector-list bug that silently drops `.is-checked` styles in browsers without `:has()`, and a mismatch between Exercise 3.1's instructions (print all 10 table rows) and what `criteria.json` actually checked (only rows 1 and 10).

## CSS `:has()` fallback (`Basics_Day7_Quiz.html`)

Combined selector lists containing `:has()` are entirely discarded by browsers that don't support it — including the `.is-checked` fallback class. Split into separate rules:

```css
/* Before — entire block dropped in browsers without :has() */
.option-row:has(input:checked),
.option-row.is-checked { ... }

/* After — independent rules; .is-checked always applies */
.option-row:has(input:checked) { ... }
.option-row.is-checked { ... }
.option-row:has(input:checked) span { color: var(--txt); font-weight: 500; }
.option-row.is-checked span { color: var(--txt); font-weight: 500; }
```

## Exercise 3.1 output contract alignment (`criteria.json` + `Basics_Day7_homework.ipynb`)

- `criteria.json` Hour 27 test now checks all 10 multiplication table lines (`Table 4 x 1 = 4` … `Table 4 x 10 = 40`) instead of just the first and last.
- Canonical output contract block in the notebook updated to match, so exercise instructions, contract, and autograder expectations are consistent.

